Package <Unnamed>

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Heuristic
    This defines the interface for all heuristics for all search problems.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ArbitraryHeuristic
    Just for testing purposes, this heuristic gives an arbitrary (but consistent) value for distance.
    DisplacementHeuristic
    This defines the displacement heuristic for the 8-Puzzle.
    ManhattanHeuristic
    This defines the Manhattan heuristic for the 8-Puzzle.
    NoHeuristic
    This is a "dummy" heuristic for use by BFS.
    Practice  
    PuzzlePath
    A path is a list of states, from start to finish.
    PuzzleState
    Represents a state (placement of tiles) of the puzzle.
    PuzzleTester
    This class provides several methods to try out various pieces of the code.
    SearchProblem
    Represents a search problem to be solved.
